args:
The party makes their way through the cave
and finds a wall engraved with ancient faerie
writing. While the others endure a fierce attack,
Notte prays desperately for the way to open.
And as she wishes to be of help to her friends,
a brilliant light spills forth from her body.
Are we sure there's a way for us to reach\nthe Faerie Kingdom inside there?
So long as it's got four walls and a roof,\nlet's get in the damn thing before these\nguys have us for lunch!
These enemies have been driven mad;\nit is unlikely they will give up the pursuit.
Guys, I DEFINITELY think we can get to\nthe Faerie Kingdom from in here!
Keep moving! Maybe we can put some\ndistance between us and them!
Aw, hell! It's a dead end!
You sure this is the right cave, Notte?
Yeah. It should be riiight around here...
Hmm... This wall appears to have some\nmanner of design engraved upon it.
Interesting. This is the language\nof the ancient faeries.
(Stand before this wall and offer up\nyour prayers, Notte.)
So I just wish for it like before, right?
But that didn't work last time...
We're going to hold them off, Notte.
You just get that gate open!
(If I don't hurry this up, my friends're all\ngonna be dragon snacks!)
(Please let us go to the Faerie Kingdom!)
Okay, don't panic, Notte. Keep your head\nin the game and just try it again...
If we stay here, I fear our disadvantage\nwill only continue to grow.
I propose we fight our way free from this\ncave while we still retain the strength\nand find a suitable place to regroup.
It will be a tough battle, but it's better\nthan being pinned in a dead end.
No, not yet! Notte can do this!
We have to give her more time.
If that is your wish, I will respect it.\nBut we cannot tarry long.
Sorry to ask this of you, Gatov.
Notte! I know you can do this.
Okay. I'm gonna try one more time!
(Okay, so it's great that I'm big now,\nbut that doesn't mean squat if I can't\npull this off right now...)
(Even though we promised the three of us\ncould overcome any hardship together...)
I still draw breath, which is more than I\nhoped for against such numbers...
We gotta hang on for Notte,\nso let's bring it to these chumps!
UGH, I'm so SICK of this crap!
Such light! Has the way opened?!
